Registration is recording of identification details mostly social on documents needed for any attendance

\section*{3. ADMISSION}

The same identification details recorded during registration is used and the ward number added on the form.

\section*{4. DISCHARGE}

This is a procedure carried out when a patient is supposed to leave the hospital after treatment.

\section*{5. Appointments}

Patients are asked to report to the various clinics on certain time and dates ready to be seen.

\section*{6. FILING}

Is a way of arranging the documents in a prescribed order or in systematic manner.

\section*{7. TRACING}

This is monitoring the movements of all the documents and their whereabouts.

\section*{8. CLINIC PREPARATION}

This is getting ready all the documents -48 hours in advance before a patient attends a clinic.

\section*{9. FOLLOW-UP OF PATIENTS}

There are some patients who still need to be monitored after they have been discharged from the hospital such as psychiatric, cancer cases etc.

\section*{10. CODING AND INDEXING}

Diseases and operations and other procedures in medicines need to be coded and indexed using the international classification of diseases, ICD and the international classification of procedures in medicine ICPM (WHO).

\section*{11. COLLECTION, TABULATION, ANALYSIS, INTERPRETATION AND DISSEMINATION OF DATA}

Raw data collected form health records are put in tables, analysed interpreted and forwarded to the users.

\section*{12. MAINTENANCE OF HEALTH RECORDS EQUIPMENT}

All the equipment used in a health records department must be maintained by the health records and information technician.

\section*{13. MAINTAIN CONFIDENTIALITY}

All the information in a health records document is confidential and should not be handled by unauthorised persons.

\section*{14. MANAGE SPECIAL HEALTH RECORDS}

There are special health records that are initiated and handled differently from other records, namely:-
(a) Psychiatric records
(b) Tuberculosis records
(c) Maternity records
(d) Sexually Transmitted diseases records
(e) HIV/AIDS

\section*{15. DESIGN MEDICAL FORMS}

All medical forms are supposed to be designed by the health records and information technician in consultation with the users

\section*{16. ENSURE QUALITY ASSURANCE OF HEALTH RECORDS}

The quality of the record will reflect the type of health care being rendered to the patient/ client.

